---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Frequently Asked Questions | Hometown Insurance Agency">

    <section class="faq-hero">
        <div class="container">
            <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
            <p>Expert answers to your most common insurance questions. We're here to provide the clarity and specialized advice you need to feel secure.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <div class="faq-main">
        <div class="container faq-grid">
            <aside class="faq-nav">
                <ul>
                    <li><a href="#general" class="active">General Information</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#fire-ems">Fire & EMS Districts</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#personal">Personal Insurance</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#claims">Claims Process</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#billing">Billing & Payments</a></li>
                </ul>
            </aside>

            <main>
                <div id="general" class="faq-section">
                    <h2>General Information</h2>
                    <div class="faq-card">
                        <div class="faq-header"><h3>Who is Hometown Insurance Agency?</h3><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></div>
                        <div class="faq-content">
                            <p>Hometown Insurance Agency is an independent insurance agency based on Long Island, NY, providing customized insurance solutions for individuals, families, and businesses, including home insurance, auto insurance, business insurance, and specialized programs for Fire and EMS districts.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-card">
                        <div class="faq-header"><h3>What types of insurance coverage do I really need?</h3><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></div>
                        <div class="faq-content">
                            <p>Your insurance needs depend on factors like your lifestyle, assets, business operations, and potential risks. A personalized review helps ensure you have the right home, auto, or business insurance coverage without paying for protection you don't need.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-card">
                        <div class="faq-header"><h3>How can an insurance advisor help beyond just finding a policy?</h3><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></div>
                        <div class="faq-content">
                            <p>An experienced insurance advisor helps identify risks, explain coverage options for home, auto, and business insurance, advocate for you during claims, and adjust your policies as your life or business evolves.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-card">
                        <div class="faq-header"><h3>How often should I review or update my insurance policies?</h3><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></div>
                        <div class="faq-content">
                            <p>It's recommended to review your home, auto, or business insurance policies at least once a year—or anytime you experience a major life or business change such as renovations, new equipment, business growth, or additional drivers or employees.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div id="fire-ems" class="faq-section">
                    <h2>Fire & EMS Districts</h2>
                    <div class="faq-card">
                        <div class="faq-header"><h3>What is LOSAP and do you provide it?</h3><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></div>
                        <div class="faq-content">
                            <p>LOSAP (Length of Service Award Program) is a benefit program designed for volunteer firefighters. Hometown Insurance provides expert LOSAP consulting and administration services, with some of the lowest administration fees available in New York State.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-card">
                        <div class="faq-header"><h3>Are volunteer members covered under our district auto policy?</h3><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></div>
                        <div class="faq-content">
                            <p>Yes. Our specialized Fire and EMS insurance programs often include coverage for members' personal vehicles while they are responding to calls or performing official duties.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div id="personal" class="faq-section">
                    <h2>Personal Insurance</h2>
                    <div class="faq-card">
                        <div class="faq-header"><h3>What's the difference between replacement cost and actual cash value?</h3><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></div>
                        <div class="faq-content">
                            <p>Replacement cost covers what it takes to replace an item today, which is common in many home insurance policies, while actual cash value factors in depreciation. Understanding the difference can significantly impact how much you receive after a claim.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-card">
                        <div class="faq-header"><h3>Can I bundle policies to save money?</h3><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></div>
                        <div class="faq-content">
                            <p>Yes. Bundling home insurance and auto insurance policies is one of the most common ways to save money, and it can also simplify managing your insurance coverage.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-card">
                        <div class="faq-header"><h3>What factors affect my insurance premiums?</h3><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></div>
                        <div class="faq-content">
                            <p>Insurance premiums for home, auto, and business insurance may be influenced by several factors, including:</p>
                            <ul style="margin-left: 20px; margin-top: 10px;">
                                <li>Location</li>
                                <li>Claims history</li>
                                <li>Coverage limits</li>
                                <li>Industry type</li>
                                <li>Property value</li>
                                <li>Safety measures</li>
                                <li>Credit history (where permitted)</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-card">
                        <div class="faq-header"><h3>Do I need umbrella or excess liability coverage?</h3><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></div>
                        <div class="faq-content">
                            <p>If you have significant assets, rental properties, or a business, umbrella liability coverage provides an additional layer of protection beyond your standard home or auto insurance policy limits.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-card">
                        <div class="faq-header"><h3>What does my policy not cover?</h3><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></div>
                        <div class="faq-content">
                            <p>Exclusions vary depending on whether it's a home, auto, or business insurance policy, but common gaps may include floods, earthquakes, cyber incidents, or certain high-value items. Reviewing your policies with an advisor can help identify and close these gaps.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div id="claims" class="faq-section">
                    <h2>Claims Process</h2>
                    <div class="faq-card">
                        <div class="faq-header"><h3>How do I file a claim, and what should I expect?</h3><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></div>
                        <div class="faq-content">
                            <p>Claims for home insurance, auto insurance, or business insurance can usually be filed online or by phone with your insurance carrier. An adjuster will review the loss, gather documentation, and guide you through the process until the claim is resolved.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div id="billing" class="faq-section">
                    <h2>Billing & Payments</h2>
                    <div class="faq-card">
                        <div class="faq-header"><h3>How do deductibles work, and how do I choose the right one?</h3><i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></div>
                        <div class="faq-content">
                            <p>A deductible is the amount you pay out of pocket before your home, auto, or business insurance coverage takes effect. Higher deductibles typically mean lower premiums, but it's important to choose an amount you're comfortable paying if a claim occurs.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </main>
        </div>
    </div>

    <section class="faq-interaction">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="interaction-grid">
                <div class="interaction-box">
                    <i class="fa-solid fa-magnifying-glass-chart"></i>
                    <h3>Explore Our Products</h3>
                    <p>Which insurance type interests you most?</p>
                    <select class="custom-select" id="productExplorer">
                        <option value="">Select a Category...</option>
                        <option value="/personal">Home & Auto Insurance</option>
                        <option value="/firefighter-ems">Fire & EMS District Coverage</option>
                        <option value="/business">Business & General Insurance</option>
                        <option value="/life-health">Life Insurance</option>
                    </select>
                </div>

                <div class="interaction-box ask-box">
                    <i class="fa-solid fa-comment-dots"></i>
                    <h3>Still have questions?</h3>
                    <p>If you couldn't find your answer, ask us directly and our team will get back to you.</p>
                    <form id="faqQuestionForm">
                        <input type="text" name="full_name" placeholder="Your Name" required style="width:100%;padding:12px 15px;border-radius:8px;border:1px solid #cbd5e1;font-size:16px;margin-top:15px;">
                        <input type="email" name="email" placeholder="Your Email" required style="width:100%;padding:12px 15px;border-radius:8px;border:1px solid #cbd5e1;font-size:16px;margin-top:10px;">
                        <textarea name="message" placeholder="Type your question here..." required style="width:100%;padding:15px;border-radius:8px;border:1px solid #cbd5e1;margin-top:10px;min-height:120px;font-family:inherit;font-size:16px;"></textarea>
                        <button type="submit" class="btn btn-red" style="width: 100%; margin-top: 20px;">Submit Question</button>
                    </form>
                    <p id="faqFormMsg" style="display:none; margin-top:10px; font-weight:700; text-align:center;"></p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <style>
        .faq-hero {
            position: relative;
            background: url('https://static-asset.amac.us/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/10094133/vintage-car.jpg') no-repeat center center;
            background-size: cover;
            color: white;
            padding: 80px 0;
            text-align: center;
        }
        .faq-hero::before {
            content: '';
            position: absolute;
            top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%;
            background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.85) 0%, rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.6) 100%);
            z-index: 1;
        }
        .faq-hero .container { position: relative; z-index: 2; }
        .faq-hero h1 { color: white; font-size: 52px; margin-bottom: 20px; text-shadow: 0 2px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.5); }
        .faq-hero p { max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; font-size: 20px; color: #cbd5e1; line-height: 1.6; }

        .faq-main { padding: 80px 0; background: var(--bg-light); }
        .faq-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 300px 1fr; gap: 50px; }

        .faq-nav { position: sticky; top: 220px; align-self: start; }
        .faq-nav ul { list-style: none; background: white; border-radius: 12px; padding: 20px; box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.05); }
        .faq-nav li { margin-bottom: 10px; }
        .faq-nav a { text-decoration: none; color: var(--text-gray); font-size: 16px; font-weight: 600; display: block; padding: 10px; border-radius: 6px; transition: 0.3s; }
        .faq-nav a:hover, .faq-nav a.active { background: var(--primary-red); color: white; }

        .faq-interaction { background: white; padding: 80px 0; border-top: 1px solid #e5e7eb; }
        .interaction-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 40px; }
        .interaction-box { background: var(--bg-light); padding: 40px; border-radius: 15px; text-align: center; }
        .interaction-box i { font-size: 40px; color: var(--primary-red); margin-bottom: 20px; }

        .custom-select { width: 100%; padding: 15px; border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid #cbd5e1; font-size: 16px; margin-top: 20px; background: white; }

        .ask-box textarea { resize: vertical; }

        @media (max-width: 992px) {
            .faq-grid, .interaction-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
            .faq-nav { display: none; }
        }
    </style>

    <script is:inline>
        // FAQ accordion toggle
        document.querySelectorAll('.faq-header').forEach(header => {
            header.addEventListener('click', () => {
                const card = header.parentElement;
                const section = card.parentElement;
                const isActive = card.classList.contains('active');
                section.querySelectorAll('.faq-card').forEach(c => c.classList.remove('active'));
                if (!isActive) card.classList.add('active');
            });
        });

        // Sidebar nav smooth scroll with active state
        document.querySelectorAll('.faq-nav a').forEach(anchor => {
            anchor.addEventListener('click', function(e) {
                e.preventDefault();
                document.querySelectorAll('.faq-nav a').forEach(a => a.classList.remove('active'));
                this.classList.add('active');
                const targetId = this.getAttribute('href');
                const targetElement = document.querySelector(targetId);

                const headerHeight = 200;
                const elementPosition = targetElement.getBoundingClientRect().top + window.pageYOffset;
                const offsetPosition = elementPosition - headerHeight;

                window.scrollTo({
                    top: offsetPosition,
                    behavior: 'smooth'
                });
            });
        });

        // Product explorer dropdown navigation
        document.getElementById('productExplorer').addEventListener('change', function() {
            const value = this.value;
            if (value) {
                location.href = value;
            }
        });

        // FAQ question form
        var faqForm = document.getElementById('faqQuestionForm');
        var faqMsg = document.getElementById('faqFormMsg');
        if (faqForm) {
            faqForm.addEventListener('submit', function(e) {
                e.preventDefault();
                var submitBtn = faqForm.querySelector('button[type="submit"]');
                var originalText = submitBtn.textContent;
                submitBtn.textContent = 'Sending...';
                submitBtn.disabled = true;
                if (faqMsg) faqMsg.style.display = 'none';

                var formData = {
                    full_name: faqForm.querySelector('input[name="full_name"]').value,
                    email: faqForm.querySelector('input[name="email"]').value,
                    message: faqForm.querySelector('textarea[name="message"]').value,
                    page: 'faq',
                    insurance_type: 'FAQ Question'
                };

                fetch('/api/lead', {
                    method: 'POST',
                    headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
                    body: JSON.stringify(formData)
                })
                .then(function(res) { return res.json(); })
                .then(function(data) {
                    if (data.success) {
                        window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
                        window.dataLayer.push({
                            event: 'form_submission',
                            form_name: 'faq',
                            insurance_type: formData.insurance_type || '',
                            contact_method: '',
                            hear_about: '',
                            help_type: ''
                        });
                        faqMsg.style.color = '#10b981';
                        faqMsg.textContent = '✓ Your question has been submitted! Our team will get back to you shortly.';
                        faqMsg.style.display = 'block';
                        faqForm.reset();
                    } else {
                        faqMsg.style.color = '#ef4444';
                        faqMsg.textContent = data.error || 'Something went wrong. Please try again.';
                        faqMsg.style.display = 'block';
                    }
                })
                .catch(function() {
                    faqMsg.style.color = '#ef4444';
                    faqMsg.textContent = 'Network error. Please try again.';
                    faqMsg.style.display = 'block';
                })
                .finally(function() {
                    submitBtn.textContent = originalText;
                    submitBtn.disabled = false;
                });
            });
        }
    </script>

</BaseLayout>
